I hate depressing ends to shows... Why are all the Chinese shows I watch always so sad????? Okay, here's a basic synopsis of the story: guy falls in love with girl, they have to fight an evil person, they make some friends who help them fight the evil person, all the friends die (except for two of the old people but that's only they're minor characters and only appear like three times during the 38 episodes of the series), the girl sacrifices herself for the guy, and the guy ends up with a baby and nothing else.

Argh. I hate whoever made up this story. Apparently it's based on some Chinese video game. At least in the game, the ending isn't as bad. Pffft.

Now I'm going to read Eldest and try and focus on something happier.
http://hanneli415.livejournal.com/8353.html

Okay, so, exciting stuff first: I get to take my road test in eight days!!! WOOHOOO!!!! Even better, I only had to do two real hours of observation - Gilli made up the rest for me!

Now onto the not so exciting news...

Summer is almost over and I'm beginning to feel depressed because I haven't really enjoyed it yet and now I only have like three weeks before I have to go back to school.

The moment I get license I'm going to take my dad's car and go visit people. He won't need it during the day. Anyone up for a trip to Providence with me? My parents want me to visit Brown still...

And I can't get on facebook with my university email. It must hate me or something.
http://hanneli415.livejournal.com/7255.html

Okay, so, I'm going to be leaving tomorrow. To go on the wonderful college trip... Yeah... Half the schools on the list are places I don't even want to go like Princeton and Cornell. But who's making me go anyway? My oh so wonderful dad.
Sure, they are good schools. But I DON'T want to go to some of them. The only consolation I have is the possibility of seeing my best friend who I haven't seen in over a year when we go to tour NYU. And yes, I do actually want to go to NYU. More so than some of the other schools. However, I'm really excited to finally be going to Johns Hopkins. My dream school... Though now I might not be getting in due to the not so happy scores I got on one of my SAT IIs. If that is the reason I don't get in, I swear I will wipe off standardized testing from the face of this earth. I don't know how I'll do it, but I will.
I want to go on a long roadtrip one day. Just get away from here, from places that I'm accustomed to. I'm sure I'll be back but I just want a little bit of adventure - journey into something totally unfamiliar.
My suitcase won't fit all my clothes since I have to share it with my sister. <sigh> My parens won't even let me have my own!
http://hanneli415.livejournal.com/6680.html

I hate standardized testing...it stinks. Even though I think I did fine on the Biology, I still despise these tests more than ever.

I had to go to Pawtucket, RI to take my test. It was really annoying. The school was really big though. All the SAT II people had to go to the cafeteria where they separated us alphabetically. The guy actually got my name right on the first try!!! However, before I was called, he announced someone else who I haven't seen in years and evidently didn't recognize when I got in. It was Zach Arbit! Ugh. And what is up with his hair??? Hopefully he didn't recognize me either.

Anyway, I have to continue studying for history. I hate history. Primary source readings are fun. But I don't like having to memorize everything about them. <sigh> Maybe tomorrow, after I'm done with everything, I won't have to take another history class ever for the rest of high school. Then again, I still want to take the course in Ancient Chinese history next spring, so maybe I won't give up on history altogether.

Weekends are the worst part of my week. I prefer being away from my house as much as possible.

My birthday is tomorrow!! Yay!!!
However, I am still stuck studying for my lab final and finishing up the revisions of my English paper. Plus, I have a feeling that something else is due but I have no idea what.
I was watching the ending of Survivor tonight and I realized how pathetic the people on the show were. Not that I didn't think they were pathetic before, it just exxagerated their patheticness even more. I mean, who would give up a million dollars just for a donut? It's pathetic. They could've at least waited for the pizza. What's even worse is how shocked people seem to be when they realize that one of their fellow game members has been voted off. I mean, if they signed up for this as a game, why do they allow any emotions interfere with what they originally set out to do? If anything, this show brings out the fakeness I see in people every day to the worst extent. Inevitably they will have to part with one another and it's pointless to try and make any connections (unless, of course, it helps you get ahead in the game). It's a harsh way of viewing human nature, but that's the "nature" of the game. After all, doesn't everyone just want to win?
So those were my thoughts about the show. And of some aspects of daily human life.
Somehow I get the feeling that my birthday is not going to be all that fun.
